Lead Data Scientist


The Lead Data Scientist works collaboratively with interdisciplinary scientists, IT and engineering professionals across the organization to solve critical problems and answer important questions that drive key decisions for our business; Fosters new game changing ideas to produce sophisticated, intelligent optimization solutions and predictive models; Works on a team as an individual contributor with other Data Scientists.

YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Lead Data Scientist, are to:

Deliver best-in-class analytics solutions for the customer-centric commercial operations of Bayer Crop Science.
Topics and domains for this role will be focused on: short-long term forecasting, pricing, market funding, and risk models.
Results will drive business decisions and significant revenue;
Develop practical, interpretable, solid and automated solutions for business problems through expertise in statistical analysis, predictive modeling, simulation, and optimization methodology by working in a highly interactive, team-oriented environment;
Inspire, lead and mentor a small team of junior data scientists;
Be the go-to person for technical questions for the broader team;
Work closely with data science teams and business partners to break down complex business problems to set strategy, identify technical gaps, and gather requirements to build feasible solutions that are impactful, accurate and customer focused;
Be creative, resourceful, detail-oriented, able to take initiatives and exercise critical thinking when it comes to problem solving;
Be a proactive member of a global data science team to champion digital transformation, help grow our culture and support our data best practice and documentation.

WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our life values, more specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

PhD in a quantitative field such as actuarial science, economics, statistics, applied mathematics, or other related quantitative discipline or Masters Degree.
Experience leading and developing junior data scientists;
Expert in conducting statistical inferences, traditional machine learning algorithms, time-series analysis and forecasting, statistical simulation, analysis using disparate sources of data;
Advanced programming skills in either R or Python, SQL for data ETL and machine-learning tasks, proficient in version-control tools;
Proven ability to inspire, build culture, and lead a small team to work with IT and business partner to deliver valuable scientific analytics solution.
Preferred Qualifications:

Experience in related fields where data science techniques are used, including agriculture and economics/econometrics and actuarial science;
Strong proficiency in predictive modeling—to include comprehension of theory, modeling/identification strategies and limitations and pitfalls;
Demonstrates basic understanding of software development best practices (Version Control, Code Documentation & Review, Cloud Based Sequence Analysis, Database Management);
Experience working with CRM tools, interactive visualization tools such as R-shiny and Tableau;
Proficient in leveraging cloud-based data science end to end pipeline through AWS, GCP, Azure, Domino, Git;
PHD with 3+ years of analytics related industry experience or Master’s degree with 7+ years of experience.
